						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken Slab built into the raised platform of the mosque near the village Chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>12th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th Century A.D.,</hi> seems to record a gift to god Kēśavadēva. It mentions Kāḷimarasa who was probably Mahāpradhāna and <hi rend="italic">Kaḍitaverggaḍe.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
